<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880804-0037 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Coastal Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CGP FREST </CO><TEXT>   Coastal Corp. said it is forming a joint venture for the ownership and operation of its West Coast refining and marketing properties with China National Chemicals Import/Export Corp.    China National is a state-owned, international business concern of China. Coastal, a Houston energy concern, said the plan calls for China National to buy a 50% stake in the venture. The price wasn't disclosed.    Properties in the venture include a Coastal-owned California refinery and fuel-oil terminals and marketing operations in California and Oregon.    The refinery has a through-put capacity of 55,000 barrels a day and storage for 2.2 million barrels, while the terminals have combined storage capacity of 1.4 million barrels of refined petroleum products.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Coastal closed at $32.375 a share, up $1.25. </TEXT></DOC>